                <h1>Boston Tea Party: A Revolutionary Protest Explained</h1>
                <p>The Boston Tea Party, a pivotal event in 1773, was a protest by American colonists against British taxation without representation. Disguised as Mohawk Indians, they boarded British ships in Boston Harbor and dumped 342 chests of tea into the water. This bold act galvanized colonial resistance and ultimately sparked the American Revolution.</p>
